Title: Solving Gauss' Laws and Searching Dirac Observables for the Four

InteractionsAuthors: Luca Lusanna (INFN Florence)

Comments: 9 pages, LaTeX (using espcrc2.sty). Talk given at the Second Conf. on

Constrained Dynamics and Quantum Gravity, S.Margherita Ligure, 17-21September 1996Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys.Proc.Suppl. 57 (1997) 13-20

A review is given of the status of the program of classical reduction toDirac's observables of the four interactions (standard SU(3)xSU(2)xU(1)particle model and tetrad gravity) with the matter described either byGrassmann-valued fermion fields or by particles with Grassmann charges.